 I put Ron Paul first here for personal reasons. The other day, as I was already late to an engagement and could not afford to waste more time stopping to buy a lighter to abate my nicotine withdrawal pains, I was forced to stop at a traffic signal in the left turn lane, where there were Ron Paul people on every grassy area of a large six lane intersection. As I pulled to a stop, I lowered my window, the nearest worker walked to my window and was about to speak as he handed me some propoganda, I said "Have you got a light?"
 
 He did and I was immediately a happy camper. I took a long drag and sighed an exhale similar to those often heard after great sex and thanked him for the help. We chatted about Ron Paul and the splash he is making. I took the printed matter and stuck it in the visor as the light turned green for me. I read it later in the evening and noticed that Mr. Paul makes a good deal of sense. Despite my pledge to never vote for a man with two first names, I'm considering him...should he make it through the gauntlets and get on a ticket anywhere. I think he might also possess Vice-Presidential meat and potatoes.
